## 3. How Tools Are Registered with Subagents/Specialists

**Three registration paths:**

| Path | Method | Scope |
|------|--------|-------|
| Extension | `pi.registerTool()` | Global via `~/.pi/agent/extensions/` or project via `.pi/extensions/` |
| SDK | `createAgentSession({ customTools: [...] })` | Programmatic, embedded apps |
| SDK | `createAgentSession({ tools: ["name1", "name2"] })` | Enable/disable by name |

**Tool activation:** Tools must be both registered AND listed in the active tools set:

```typescript
// Extension manages active tools
pi.setActiveTools(["read", "bash", "my_tool"]);
pi.getActiveTools();    // string[]
pi.getAllTools();       // ToolInfo[] (name, description, parameters, promptGuidelines, sourceInfo)
```

**Dynamic registration at runtime** (see `dynamic-tools.ts`):
```typescript
pi.on("session_start", (_event, ctx) => {
  pi.registerTool({ ... });  // Register during startup or later
});
```

**Overriding built-in tools:** Register a tool with the same name as a built-in. Renderer inheritance is per-slot — omit `renderCall`/`renderResult` to keep the built-in's UI while overriding execution:

```typescript
pi.registerTool({
  name: "read",  // Same name → overrides built-in read
  // ...custom execute...
  // No renderCall/renderResult → built-in renderer used
});
```

**First registration wins** within extensions — the first extension to register a tool name gets it; later registrations with the same name are silently ignored.

